data.value: The artist is reflecting on his own life and how he wishes his scars are visible so others can understand. He also has a more sarcastic outlook on others and has resigned himself to dealing with loneliness.
Metaphor, Personification
Sadness, Loneliness
“Scar tissue”, “birds”
Verse
The time period of this song is uncertain. It could refer to a modern time or a more abstract time.
The artist is reflecting on his own life while feeling lonely, observing the birds, and wanting to share his life with others.

The song suggests that in order to connect with others and truly connect with the world, we must be willing to open up and expose our vulnerability. This could be a metaphor for how it is important to be honest and transparent in our relationships.
